<p>Here is the full syntax of a tests file, in case you need it to integrate with a third-party tool:</p>

<dl class="format">
	<dt>file</dt><dd><img src="<:url "support/tests-file/file.png":>" width="237" height="50"></dd>
	<dt>preamble</dt><dd><img src="<:url "support/tests-file/preamble.png":>" width="351" height="68"></dd>
	<dt>namespace</dt><dd><img src="<:url "support/tests-file/namespace.png":>" width="249" height="36"></dd>
	<dt>use</dt><dd><img src="<:url "support/tests-file/use.png":>" width="353" height="68"></dd>
	<dt>section</dt><dd><img src="<:url "support/tests-file/section.png":>" width="189" height="50"></dd>
	<dt>test</dt><dd><img src="<:url "support/tests-file/test.png":>" width="171" height="36"></dd>
	<dt>case</dt><dd><img src="<:url "support/tests-file/case.png":>" width="207" height="68"></dd>
	<dt>input</dt><dd><img src="<:url "support/tests-file/input.png":>" width="179" height="36"></dd>
	<dt>output</dt><dd><img src="<:url "support/tests-file/output.png":>" width="189" height="36"></dd>
</dl>

<p>Note that you can always use multi-line comments anywhere within a file.</p>
